title: Biophysical characterization of the SARS-CoV-2 spike protein binding with the ACE2 receptor and implications for infectivity
author: Ratul Chowdhury, and Costas D. Maranas
affiliations: Department of Chemical Engineering, The Pennsylvania State University, University Park. PA 16802
abstract: SARS-CoV-2 is a novel highly virulent pathogen which gains entry to human cells by binding with the 12 cell surface receptor – angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE2). We computationally contrasted the 13 binding interactions between human ACE2 and coronavirus spike protein receptor binding domain (RBD)
